#' BayesR - Gibbs sampling for BayesR model
#'
#' This function performs Gibbs sampling to estimate the parameters of Bayesian  multiple linear regression model with mixture of Gaussians and discrete spike at zero.
#' The method saves memory by saving the samples after burn_in into a the outputFile in csv format using a single thread for sampling and a single thread for storing samples.
#'
#' @param outputFile The file where samples will be stored. First row of the file contains variable name, fields are separated by commas.
#' @param seed  Random seed.
#' @param max_iterations Total number of samples for the Gibbs sampler (including burn_in)
#' @param burn_in  Integer less than max_iterations, samples from 1 to burn_in will be considered as burn_in and not saved.
#' @param thinning Integer, thinning regime, after burn_in this value determines how many samples are skipped until next sample is saved.
#' @param X Design matrix, with variables in the columns and individuals in the rows, preferably each column should be centered and scaled to std 1.
#' @param Y Dependant variable, one vector of same length as number of rows in X. Preferably centered and scaled.
#' @param sigma0 Prior over the intercept parameter
#' @param v0E  Degrees of freedom of the inv-scaled-chisquared distribution prior over the residuals variance.
#' @param s02E Scale parameter of the inv-scaled-chisquared distribution prior over the residuals variance.
#' @param v0G Degrees of freedom of the inv-scaled-chisquared distribution prior over the effects variance parameter.
#' @param s02G Scale of the inv-scaled-chisquared distribution prior over the effects variance parameter.
#' @param cva  Vector of the non-zero mixture variances of the BayesR model.
#'
#' @return All samples saved in outputFile
#' @export
#'
#' @examples
BayesRSamplerV2 <- function(outputFile, seed, max_iterations, burn_in, thinning, X, Y, sigma0, v0E, s02E, v0G, s02G, cva) {
    invisible(.Call(`_BayesRRcpp_BayesRSamplerV2`, outputFile, seed, max_iterations, burn_in, thinning, X, Y, sigma0, v0E, s02E, v0G, s02G, cva))
}

